<DOC><DOCNO> AP890913-0120 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-13-89 1238EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BoatPeople     09-13 0148</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Boat People,0150</SECOND><HEAD>53 Boat People Arrested in Connection With Island Riot</HEAD><DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Police arrested 53 Vietnamese boat peoplesuspected of robbery, rape and other crimes during unrest on theisland where they had been housed, authorities said Wednesday.   The arrested Vietnamese were among about 5,000 boat people placedon Tai A Chau island after sailing into this British colony seekingrefuge from their Communist homeland.   Violence on the island broke out last month. When police arrived,they said about 1,000 Vietnamese threw stones at them. The policefired tear gas to disperse the mob and then left the island.   Senior police official Gregory Lam told local radio that 17 casesof rape were reported during the island disturbance. Eight peoplewere arrested in connection with 12 of the cases, he said.   Tai A Chau was evacuated earlier this month after a choleraoutbreak.</TEXT></DOC>